You will need to create two separate configuration files: 
one for the Primary unit and one for the Secondary unit. 
The configurations are nearly identical, with the priority value determining which firewall acts as the active unit (higher number = higher priority).
After initial configuration (assigning ip address to physical interface, routing, nat, firewall policies, security profiles.)
Configuring Active - Passive
Before Configuring need to check both should have same model device, version and License.
# Primary FortiGate HA Configuration
config system ha
    set group-name "FortiGate-HA-Cluster"
    set mode a-p
    set password "YourSecureHAPassword123!"
    set hbdev "port3" 50 "port4" 50
    set session-pickup enable
    set override disable
    set priority 200
    set monitor "port1" "port2"
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secondary FortiGate HA Configuration
config system ha
    set group-name "FortiGate-HA-Cluster"
    set mode a-p
    set password "YourSecureHAPassword123!"
    set hbdev "port3" 50 "port4" 50
    set session-pickup enable
    set override disable
    set priority 100
    set monitor "port1" "port2"

The heartbeat interfaces (e.g., port3 and port4). It is best practice to use two dedicated cables for redundancy.
Ensures that active sessions (like file transfers or phone calls) don't drop during a failover event.
The interfaces that the HA process watches. If port1 (e.g., your WAN) goes down on the primary, it will trigger a failover.
